{
  "name": "SetToolTransformOverride",
  "arguments": [
    {
      "name": "transform",
      "desc": "Tool body transform",
      "optional": false,
      "type": "TTransform"
    }
  ],
  "returns": [],
  "examples": [
    [
      "function init()",
      "",
      "\tif GetBool(\"game.thirdperson\") then",
      "\t\tlocal toolTransform = Transform(Vec(0.3, -0.3, -0.2), Quat(0.0, 0.0, 15.0))",
      "",
      "\t\t-- Rotate around point",
      "\t\tlocal pivotPoint = Vec(-0.01, -0.2, 0.04)",
      "\t\ttoolTransform.pos = VecSub(toolTransform.pos, pivotPoint)",
      "\t\tlocal rotation = Transform(Vec(), QuatAxisAngle(Vec(0,0,1), GetPlayerPitch()))",
      "\t\ttoolTransform = TransformToParentTransform(rotation, toolTransform)",
      "\t\ttoolTransform.pos = VecAdd(toolTransform.pos, pivotPoint)",
      "",
      "\t\tSetToolTransformOverride(toolTransform)",
      "\telse",
      "\t\tlocal toolTransform = Transform(Vec(0.3, -0.3, -0.2), Quat(0.0, 0.0, 15.0))",
      "\t\tSetToolTransform(toolTransform)",
      "\tend",
      "end"
    ]
  ],
  "description": [
    "This function serves as an alternative to SetToolTransform, providing full control over tool animation by disabling all internal tool animations. ",
    "When using this function, you must manually include pitch, sway, and crouch movements in the transform. To maintain this control, call the function every frame from the tick function."
  ]
}